title: Another Deadly Quake Rocks an Already Ravaged Area of Turkey
description: Just two weeks after the deadliest earthquake in the country’s modern history, a powerful shock hit southern Turkey, where many people are still sleeping outdoors for fear of building collapses.

title: A Year of War in Ukraine: A Guide to the Conflict
description: On the first anniversary of the invasion, here’s a guide to how the biggest war in Europe since World War II came about, and what’s at stake for Russia and the world.

title: Your Tuesday Briefing: Biden Travels to Kyiv
description: Also, another earthquake strikes Turkey and Syria.

title: Biden’s Kyiv Visit Lifts Spirits of War-Weary Ukrainians
description: The American president was the most prominent Western leader to visit Ukraine since Russia invaded, and the capital was swept up in the excitement.

title: On Blinken Visit, Quake Relief Soothes U.S.-Turkey Tensions
description: Secretary of State Antony J. Blinken pledged to keep helping Turkey recover from a devastating earthquake, but there were few hints of progress on disputes over F-16 sales and NATO.

title: Nicola Bulley’s Body Is Found, U.K. Police Say
description: The disappearance of Nicola Bulley, a 45-year-old mortgage adviser and mother of two, prompted a national debate over privacy and the treatment of missing women.

title: 6.3-Magnitude Earthquake Strikes Southern Turkey
description: The 6.3-magnitude quake struck near a town in hard-hit Hatay Province, one of the areas most devastated by the Feb. 6 quake that killed more than 46,000 people across Turkey and northwestern Syria.

title: In Biden’s Unannounced Visit to Kyiv, a Preview of an Increasingly Direct Contest With Putin
description: The vastly different world views of President Biden and President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia will become vividly apparent in a rare split-screen moment on Tuesday.

title: Biden Visits Kyiv, Ukraine’s Embattled Capital, as Air-Raid Siren Sounds
description: President Biden took a nearly 10-hour train ride from the border of Poland to show his administration’s “unwavering support” nearly a year into Russia’s invasion.

title: Despite War, Ukrainian Dance Group Returns for the ‘America’s Got Talent’ Finale
description: Scattered around the globe by the conflict, the group pulled together enough performers and came up with a winning routine in five days.

title: China Says U.S. Is ‘Not Qualified’ to Issue Orders on Arms
description: Beijing is trying to preserve ties with Moscow while asserting it is a neutral observer trying only to coax Russia and Ukraine into peace talks.

title: With an Eye on China, Philippines Moves Closer to U.S. Interests
description: Driven by worry about China’s aggression, President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. has adopted the most muscular foreign policy approach that the Philippines has seen in close to a decade.

title: How Biden Thinks
description: On Presidents’ Day, we go inside the West Wing to explain a crucial way that Biden is different from many Democrats.

title: Live Updates: Biden Pledges More Aid in Surprise Visit to Ukraine
description: President Biden made an unannounced visit to Kyiv, where he met with President Volodymyr Zelensky in a dramatic show of support days before the anniversary of Russia’s invasion.

title: Protesters Head to Jerusalem as Israel’s Leaders Look to Rein in Judges
description: Two contentious bills were scheduled to come up for an initial vote in Israel’s Parliament on Monday, including one that would reduce the power of the Supreme Court.

title: China Says U.S. Is ‘Not Qualified’ to Issue Orders on Arms

title: They Were Married. They Shared a Trench. They Died in It Together.
description: Taras and Olha Melster signed up to help the war effort. Like many other urban professionals in Ukraine, they never expected to be sent to the front line.

title: Nobel Peace Prize Winner Juan Manuel Santos Criticizes West’s Focus on Ukraine
description: Juan Manuel Santos, a former president of Colombia, said the Ukraine war was “sucking all the energy” away from fighting other challenges, including climate change.
